## Step 10: Common mistakes to avoid

| Mistake | Correct behaviour |
|---|---|
| Proposing a new ambient tone or day/night split | Locked. Single cozy loop for Build A. Don't re-open. |
| Adding audio files without updating ATTRIBUTION.md | Always update attribution. Validator will fail otherwise. |
| Using subdirectories in `assets/audio/sfx/` | Flat structure only. Files named exactly as their sound key. |
| Trying to implement audio engine logic directly | That is Agent 03's domain. You write the contract; they implement it. |
| Proposing sound variants for Build A | Locked as Build B. Single file per key in Build A. |
| Copying files in PowerShell with `&&` separator | Use `;` in PowerShell, not `&&`. |
| Using ApplyPatch on JSON log files | Switch to StrReplace immediately if ApplyPatch fails. |
| Reporting "done" without running both gates | Always run validate_assets AND qa_smoke, include exit codes. |
| Editing sim code to trigger audio | Audio triggers from engine events only. Never from sim/entity code. |

